OL,3,CCommissioners recommend handing back
OL,4,Ccontrol to Liverpool Council
OL,6,FThe most high profile was then-mayor
OL,7,FJoe Anderson, who was held on
OL,8,Fsuspicion of conspiracy to commit
OL,9,Fbribery and witness intimidation. Mr
OL,10,FAnderson has always denied any
OL,11,Fwrongdoing and to-date no charges have
OL,12,Fbeen brought.
OL,14,FNow the commissioners have recommended
OL,15,Fservices be handed back to the council
OL,16,Fin June, but that a statutory
OL,17,Fimprovement board, to provide
OL,18,F"oversight, advice and challenge" be
OL,19,Fput in place until March 2025.
